<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,406,1474,1500]" box="[189,406,1474,1500]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,406,1474,1500]" fontSize="11" level="4" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" reason="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,406,1474,1500]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Short description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,1398,1521,1653]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Epiphytic; long-creeping filiform rhizomes, rootless and densely covered by dense black trichomes, bearing widely separated fronds; fronds sessile and peltate, up to 6 cm long, mostly round and entire, with false veins parallel to true veins and palmate venation; sori numerous, pantotactic, cylindrical with a truncated mouth.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
